{"id":"ev_3822026aa6e741a7","runId":"run_282","type":"delegation","at":1782681777921,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_46dd47b2dbb24a70","atom":0,"task":"Build a one-time legacy-local-runs CLEANUP INVENTORY tool as a standalone script `scripts/cleanup-legacy-local-runs.mjs`. This atom builds ONLY the non-destructive dry-run/report path; the destructive purge/backfill execution is a later atom gated on founder approval. This advances ticket 0082.\n\nWHAT TO BUILD:\n- A node script (model store access on existing `scripts/proof-retention-integration.mjs` and `scripts/observe-retention-live.mjs`) that opens the LIVE local store (`local/cocoder.db`) read-only and enumerates every cocoder local run.\n- For each run, classify against three live signals: (1) projected-to-repo? (2) workspace-resolvable? (3) terminal status?\n  * MUST REUSE the retention engine's existing projection contract — import and call `projectionCheckerFor` / `readPortableRunById` from `packages/core/src/runner/retention-plan.js` and the existing workspace resolver. Do NOT re-implement or copy the projection/resolution logic (one-owner / elegance rule). If a public entry isn't exported for script use, add a minimal export rather than duplicating the predicate.\n- Categorize the residue into: (A) pre-projection (terminal, resolvable workspace, but no portable `cocoder/runs/` record), (B) orphan-workspace (workspace absent from the registry — e.g. `job-hunt`, `test-cobuilder`, `copublisher`), (C) both.\n- HARD SAFETY INVARIANT: any run whose status is non-terminal/live MUST be excluded from all residue categories. The report must print the count of live runs excluded and list their IDs, so it is provable nothing live is ever selected.\n- Emit a LOGGED manifest (no silent action): write a timestamped manifest file (path printed to stdout, e.g. under `local/` or a logs dir) listing the exact run IDs, their local run dir paths, store row presence, category, and — for category (A) — whether the run is backfill-salvageable (has enough stored data to project a portable record). Also print a human summary: totals per category, current local run count, projected `cocoder/runs/` count, and the post-cleanup footprint each path would yield.\n\nDEFAULT MODE IS DRY-RUN/REPORT ONLY: this atom performs NO deletion, NO DB mutation, NO backfill, and NO writes other than the manifest/log file. Make it idempotent (re-running produces the same classification, only a new timestamped manifest) and bounded.\n\nWHAT MUST NOT BREAK:\n- Do NOT change the retention engine's runtime behavior or expand its boot-time GC scope (ticket 0082 note) — this is a standalone one-time tool.\n- Any source export you add for reuse must not alter existing retention behavior; existing retention tests must still pass.\n- Run `pnpm -C 'packages/core' typecheck` (or the repo's typecheck) and the retention test suite; report exact commands and outputs.\n\nACCEPTANCE: `node scripts/cleanup-legacy-local-runs.mjs` runs clean against the live store, prints the category summary + live-excluded proof, and writes a manifest file whose path it reports. No destructive action occurs. Provide the actual stdout and the written manifest path as evidence."}}
